hese from true research tokens.\r\n","name":"& C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379075963}}
{"type":"message","id":"7317fc23","parentId":"157d9015","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:04:35.967Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bhfzr4jmii9y_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 150318\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiments/hybrid_scoring_experiment.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's been significant work done on CFI compression experiments\r\n3. The key pending item is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to run the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment that was designed in the previous session. This directly follows from the \"Constant Format Problem\" insight - that pure CFI thresholding fails because tokens like \"for next instantiation\" appear in every pulse with CFI=1.0.\r\n\r\nThe experiment design is already documented:\r\n- Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Test on 200 pulses, 80/20 split\r\n- Compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nI should create a script or documentation to run this experiment. Let me check what exists:\r\n\r\nLooking at `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`, the next experiment is clearly defined. I should implement this experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, I need to think about what I can do in one pulse. The goal is to advance toward the hybrid experiment. The best concrete action would be to either:\r\n1. Create a script that implements the hybrid scoring formula\r\n2. Document the experiment protocol\r\n3. Start running the experiment\r\n\r\nLet me create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Calculates the hybrid score = CFI × min(1, freq/120)\r\n3. Compares it against the binary thresholds\r\n4. Outputs the comparison results\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script to run this experiment since that's the established tooling.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) is the immediate next step per the research plan. The formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) should distinguish \"constant format\" tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5). A working experiment script needs to be created.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/cfi_hybrid_experiment.ps1` implementing Strategy C: the multiplicative scoring formula that combines CFI and frequency into a single score, ready to run on the pulse corpus.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n# ========================================================\r\n# Goal: Test if multiplicative scoring distinguishes constant-format from research tokens\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== CFI×Freq Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C) ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Constants\r\n$MIN_CFI = 0.5\r\n$MIN_FREQ = 3\r\n$MAX_FREQ = 120\r\n$CORPUS_PATH = \"research/pulse_corpus\"\r\n\r\n# Hybrid scoring formula\r\n# score(T) = CFI(T) * min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Rationale: tokens with freq=160 get score=CFI*1=CFI (but 160/120=1.33, capped)\r\n#            tokens with freq=120 get score=CFI*1=CFI\r\n#            tokens with freq=60 get score=CFI*0.5 (half weight)\r\n#            tokens with freq=30 get score=CFI*0.25 (quarter weight)\r\nfunction Get-HybridScore {\r\n    param($cfi, $freq)\r\n    $freqFactor = [Math]::Min(1.0, $freq / 120.0)\r\n    return $cfi * $freqFactor\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Parse pulse token data (simulated - will read from actual pulses)\r\nfunction Get-PulseTokens {\r\n    param($pulsePath)\r\n    $tokens = @{}\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulsePath -Raw\r\n    # Extract tokens with their counts (simulated format)\r\n    # Real implementation would parse actual pulse structure\r\n    return $tokens\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Load corpus\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading pulse corpus from: $CORPUS_PATH\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\nif (-not (Test-Path $CORPUS_PATH)) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: Corpus not found at $CORPUS_PATH\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    Write-Host \"Creating directory...\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $CORPUS_PATH -Force | Out-Null\r\n}\r\n\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $CORPUS_PATH -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($pulseFiles.Count) pulses\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Token aggregation\r\n$globalTokenStats = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulse.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Extract tokens from pulse (simplified - assumes tokenized format)\r\n    # In real impl: parse tokens from pulse structure\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\"\r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        if ($line -match '^\\s*-\\s+\"([^\"]+)\"') {\r\n            $token = $matches[1]\r\n            if ($globalTokenStats.ContainsKey($token)) {\r\n                $globalTokenStats[$token].freq++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $globalTokenStats[$token] = @{\r\n                    freq = 1\r\n                    pulses = @($pulse.Name)\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Total unique tokens collected: $($globalTokenStats.Count)\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI for each token\r\n# CFI = pulses_with_token / total_pulses\r\n$totalPulses = $pulseFiles\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:03:44\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379075965}}
