{"type":"message","id":"2384345d","parentId":"bbc39286","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:04:46.593Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2iv0y7tywydd_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\n**Status:** RUNNING\n\n## Experiment Design\n\n### Hypothesis\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 BUT capped at freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33 → min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 → score = 1.0\n- Favor research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → moderate score based on both dimensions\n- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" from \"Phase 1\" based on frequency normalization\n\n### Formula Implementation\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * freq_normalized\n```\n\n### Token Scoring Examples\n| Token | CFI | Freq | freq/120 | Hybrid Score | Classification |\n|-------|-----|------|----------|--------------|----------------|\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.33→1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 1.13→1.0 | 0.96 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"research\" | 0.75 | 80 | 0.67 | 0.50 | Trajectory (allow) |\n| \"architecture\" | 0.60 | 40 | 0.33 | 0.20 | Trajectory (allow) |\n\n### Key Insight\nThe min(1, freq/120) caps the frequency contribution, so even freq=160 tokens score at most 1.0 on the frequency axis, but they still get the CFI bonus. Wait—that's not right for penalizing constants.\n\n### Revised Formula Logic\nActually, we want HIGH scores for research trajectory tokens and LOW scores for constants. Let's reconsider:\n\nIf freq(T) = 160 (constants):\n- min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\n- CFI(constants) ≈ 1.0\n- score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (HIGH)\n\nIf freq(T) = 40 (research tokens):\n- min(1, 40/120) = 0.33\n- CFI(research) ≈ 0.60\n- score = 0.60 × 0.33 = 0.20 (LOW)\n\nThis is BACKWARDS. High scores go to constants.\n\n### Corrected Formula for Penalizing Constants\nWe want constants to score LOW:\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    freq_penalty = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_penalty)  # Low freq → high score, High freq → low score\n```\n\nNow:\n- freq=160: score = 1.0 × (1 - 1.0) = 0.0 (PENALIZED)\n- freq=40: score = 0.6 × (1 - 0.33) = 0.6 × 0.67 = 0.40 (REWARDED)\n\n### Final Formula\n```python\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n    \"\"\"\n    score(T) = CFI(T) × (1 - min(1, freq(T)/120))\n    \n    High CFI + Low freq = HIGH score (research trajectory)\n    High CFI + High freq = LOW score (constant format)\n    \"\"\"\n    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_normalized)\n```\n\n## Experiment Results (TBD)\nWill run on 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:42:02\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n\n[62 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774379086591}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf588746","parentId":"2384345d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:04:56.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse correctly identified a flaw in the formula logic and corrected it. The initial formula `score = CFI × min(1, freq/120)` was backwards — it gave HIGH scores to constants (high CFI, high freq) and LOW scores to research tokens (moderate CFI, low freq). The corrected formula uses `(1 - min(1, freq/120))` as the frequency component, so high-frequency constants get penalized while low-frequency research tokens get rewarded.\n\nLet me summarize the pulse results.","thinkingSignature":"039ac39c9b4b3454b7b17691e82b4bae78c698cdf5f6aa1a5b9bd578b0123c2d"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse — 2026-03-24 15:03 UTC**\n\n---\n\n**What happened:**\n\n1. **File created:** `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` — a design doc for Strategy C (CFI×Freq hybrid scoring)\n\n2. **Key self-correction caught mid-file:** The initial hybrid formula was flawed:\n   - ❌ `score = CFI × min(1, freq/120)` — gives **HIGH** scores to constant-format tokens (high freq × high CFI = 1.0) and **LOW** scores to research tokens (low freq × moderate CFI = 0.20)\n   - ✅ Corrected to: `score = CFI × (1 - min(1, freq/120))` — high-freq constants get **penalized** (score → 0), low-freq research tokens get **rewarded**\n\n3. **Result:** Constants like \"for next instantiation\" (freq=160, CFI=1.0) now score **0.0**; research tokens like \"architecture\" (freq=40, CFI=0.60) score **0.40** — the desired separation\n\n4. **Status:** Experiment doc is staged but experiment itself is not yet run on the corpus\n\n**Pending for next pulse:** Execute the corrected hybrid scoring against the pulse corpus (200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4395,"output":404,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17044,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774379086594}}
